library for checking syntax of restructuredtext and code blocks nested within it.

see the full documentation at `read-the-docs`_


.. contents::


installation
============

from pip

.. code:: shell

    $ pip install rstcheck_core

to use pyproject.toml for configuration::

    $ pip install rstcheck_core[toml]

to add sphinx support::

    $ pip install rstcheck_core[sphinx]

to add yaml checking support::

    $ pip install rstcheck_core[yaml]

supported languages in code blocks
==================================

- bash
- doctest
- c (c99)
- c++ (c++11)
- json
- xml
- python
- restructuredtext
- yaml


.. _read-the-docs: https://rstcheck-core.readthedocs.io

documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) page for "rstcheck-core," a library version 1.2.0 released on November 13, 2023. It is designed for checking the syntax of reStructuredText and code blocks nested within it. The library requires Python version 3.8 or higher and supports several programming languages in code blocks, including Bash, C, C++, JSON, XML, Python, reStructuredText, and YAML. Installation instructions are provided for different configurations, including support for Sphinx and YAML checking.
